  "market_context": "On the NASDAQ daily chart, three days of expansion formed a swing low that reversed into a fair value gap which held as support. Price closed over previous day high, setting up a bullish bias and a draw to the next previous day high liquidity.",
  "key_observation": "London consolidated without reaching a higher time frame PD array, then 8:30 produced a manipulation higher followed by a manipulation lower; at the New York open, a CISD over the down-close candle confirmed bullish intent toward the previous day high.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily chart, identify 3 days of expansion, a swing low reversal into a supporting fair value gap, and a close above previous day high — anticipating a reach for the next previous day high.",
    "Step 2: Drop to the 15-minute chart and observe London merely consolidating without displacing to any HTF key level.",
    "Step 3: Anticipate manipulation at either 8:30 or 9:30; at 8:30 price first manipulates higher, signaling to look for a move lower.",
    "Step 4: Drop to the 5-minute chart; price sweeps the prior low but fails to displace below it.",
    "Step 5: At the New York open, price closes over the down-close candle — a change in state of delivery (CISD) confirming bullish continuation.",
    "Step 6: Frame a long entry with stop on the manipulation low and target set at the previous day high."
  ],
  "outcome": "Entry filled, trade reached previous day high target successfully.",
  "lessons": "When London consolidates without reaching an HTF level, anticipate New York to manipulate the London range. A CISD at New York open after a failed displacement provides a high-probability entry targeting the next external liquidity level such as previous day high.",
